snippet.textDisplay: I googled the difference between baking soda and powder: While both products appear similar, they're certainly not the same. Baking soda is sodium bicarbonate, which requires an acid and a liquid to become activated and help baked goods rise. Conversely, baking powder includes sodium bicarbonate, as well as an acid. It only needs a liquid to become activated.

snippet.textDisplay: Haven't read through all 4k comments, but to fill a piping bag easier, set it with the tip bent at an angle (like the bag folded so the filling doesn't come out) in a glass. Fold the ends over the rim of the glass and then it's super easy to fill it! And it's nice for storing while you're doing other things in the kitchen.
